LONELY

Today, the day of lovers, the day to spread love, the day to be loved and it’s the loneliest day for me every year. I could just stay away from social media all day and wallow in my sorrows alone but I wanted to share something with the people that see me as an upbeat, generally happy person. 5 years ago today I was laying in a hospital bed in active labor for 19 hours. Truly the longest, hardest road for me after being admitted to the hospital 27 days prior with the fear of possibly losing my children that were still in my belly. That day 5 years ago I came to the terms that if my kids were to survive, they would be my only valentines that ever actually mattered. And although they love me deeply, this is still a very hard pill to swallow. Truth is, i’m hard to love. I have very high expectations of my partner and I fall in love with the potential of others. That love is not always reciprocated by the ones I choose, hence why I am still single, but deep down I’m the biggest softy that loves to be adored by the man I love with a sprinkle of flowers here and there. 

So you see these photos, this bright, happy woman who exudes confidence and strives to make others around her feel loved and cherished yet I am empty inside. I have cried more times than I can count today and it’s not even noon yet. I’m sharing this with you all so you can see how human I truly am. So you can see that it’s ok to FEEL! I know god is teaching me about me daily and I am just trying to be receptive and obedient and stay the path. 

I’ll be better later hopefully, and as happy as it gets tomorrow, 2/15 the day I gave birth to my 2 biggest blessings but today, I’m just going to feel.
